article.headline: Davidson 90, Elon 78
article.story: ELON, N.C. -- Stephen Curry scored 26 points, reached the 2,500-point mark for his career and helped Davidson beat Elon 90-78 on Monday night. The nation's leading scorer hit the 20-point mark for the 15th straight game to lead the Wildcats (25-6, 18-2 Southern Conference). They shot 63 percent in the second half while at times revving up the potent offense that carried them within a missed 3-pointer of last year's Final Four. Now they're ready for the ride to begin again, starting with a bid later this week to claim a fourth straight SoCon tournament title. Bryant Barr scored 18 points, Steve Rossiter added 17 and Will Archambault finished with 13 for Davidson, which won its third straight overall by claiming its 14th consecutive victory in the series. Monty Sanders scored 17 points, Brett James had 16 and Ola Atoyebi had 13 for the Phoenix (10-19, 7-13).
